extends home_layout

block content
  title - What To Watch Movies - Home
  include includes/loading_modal.pug
  include includes/login_modal.pug
  // Full Page Image Header with Vertically Centered Content
  #loader(style="display:none")
  header.home_masthead#masthead_load(style="background-image: url('/images/movie_background_dark.png')")
    .container-fluid.h-100.align-items-center(style="display: flex")
      .row.mx-auto
        .col-xl-10.col-lg-8.col-md-10.col-sm-10.col-12.offset-0.offset-sm-1.offset-md-1.offset-xl-1.offset-lg-2.text-center
          img(src='/images/what_to_watch_white1.webp' alt="What To Watch Icon" style="width: 60%")
          h1.home_title.custom_heading.white_text Movie Recommendations for you. 
          p.lead.white_text(style="margin-top: 10px") The only place to go for movie recommendations.
          button.btn.custom_button#getStartedBtn Get Started
  
  .container-fluid(style="margin-top: 40px;padding-top: 30px;padding-bottom: 40px;")
    .row.curved-div.reveal(style="padding-top: 40px;background-color:#000")
      .col-12.col-sm-10.col-md-5.col-lg-5.col-xl-3.offset-xl-2.offset-lg-1.offset-md-1.offset-0.row_style
        h3.white_text.sub_heading
          | Our Philosophy. üçø
        p.white_text
          | Our aim is to provide a simple way to generate movie recommendations tailored to each individual user. Everyone has at spent at least an evening or two scrolling through movies on Netflix or Amazon Prime not knowing what to watch. We want to make this as easy as possible.   
        //- p.white_text
        //-   | As with anything, the more you rate, the more accurate we get. This works for movies you dont like as well. Not a fan of Marvel? If we can identify these kind of trends we'll try our best to avoid recommending similar movies.
      .col-12.col-sm-10.col-md-5.col-lg-5.col-xl-3.offset-xl-2.offset-lg-1.offset-md-1.offset-0.row_style
        h3.white_text.sub_heading
          | How it works. üçø
        //- p.white_text
        //-   | What we do is ask every user to rate five of their favorite movies. Once we get that many we can start generating recommendations. 
        p.white_text
          | All the recommended movies are assigned a weight. This weight indicates how much we think you'd enjoy the movie. The higher the weight, the more we think you'll like it. As you rate more movies the weight will change for each of the movies you haven't yet rated.

    .row.curved-div.reveal(style="padding-top: 20px;background-color:#000;padding-bottom: 40px")
      .col-12.col-sm-10.col-md-5.col-lg-3.col-xl-2.offset-xl-2.offset-lg-1.offset-md-1.offset-0.row_style
        h5.white_text.sub_heading
          | 908,378
        p.white_text
          | The total number of movies to choose from.   
      .col-12.col-sm-10.col-md-5.col-lg-3.col-xl-2.offset-xl-1.offset-lg-1.offset-md-1.offset-0.row_style
        h5.white_text.sub_heading
          | 167,975
        p.white_text
          | The total number of television shows we can select for you. 
      
      .col-12.col-sm-10.col-md-5.col-lg-3.col-xl-2.offset-xl-1.offset-lg-1.offset-md-1.offset-0.row_style
        h5.white_text.sub_heading
          | 10+
        p.white_text
          | The number of calculations run by our algorithm for each recommendation.

    svg(xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewbox='0 0 1440 400' style="background-image: url('/images/top2.webp')").parallax
