  .container-fluid(style="margin-top: 0px;padding-top: 30px;padding-bottom: 40px;")
    .row.curved-div(style="margin-top: 0px;padding-top: 40px;padding-bottom:20px")
      .col-12.col-sm-10.col-md-6.col-lg-6.col-xl-4.offset-xl-1.offset-lg-1.offset-md-0.offset-sm-1.offset-0.row_style
        h3.white_text.sub_heading.reveal(style="margin-bottom: 20px;text-align:center")
          | Where do we get the data? 
        p.white_text.reveal.desc_text
          | üíæ We use the&nbsp; #[a(href="https://developers.themoviedb.org/3/getting-started/introduction" target="_blank") TMDB API] to get our data on millions of movies. It's one of the worlds largest movie and TV databases that gives us access to an unreal amount of content.
        p.white_text.reveal.desc_text
          | We also use&nbsp; #[a(href="https://www.justwatch.com/" target="_blank") JustWatch] help us with our data around watch providers. They provide the ability, through TMDB, to get the watch providers for streaming, renting and buying for many many countries.
        p.white_text.reveal.desc_text
          | Combining this API with information given from you we can calculate the movies we think you would like. The calculations used are constantly evolving and so we are always looking for feedback on how well it works.
        p.white_text.reveal.desc_text  
          | We are also conscious that when signing up no one wants to spend half their evening rating movies. This is why we start gives recommendations after only rating 5 movies.
        p.white_text.reveal.desc_text  
          | We have a lot of people to thank for some of the content we use, no more so than TMDB but also a lot of the content creators over on #[a(href="https://unsplash.com/" target="_blank") Unsplash]. 

      .col-10.col-sm-10.col-md-6.col-lg-5.col-xl-4.offset-xl-2.offset-lg-0.offset-md-0.offset-1.align-self-center.row_style.desktop_show
        img(src='/images/samuel-regan-asante-wMkaMXTJjlQ-unsplash.jpg', style="width:100%").reveal

      svg(xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewbox='0 0 1440 400' style="background-image: url('/images/bottom2.webp')").parallax
        path(fill='#0e0e0e' fill-opacity='1' d='M0,160L48,133.3C96,107,192,53,288,58.7C384,64,480,128,576,144C672,160,768,128,864,138.7C960,149,1056,203,1152,192C1248,181,1344,107,1392,69.3L1440,32L1440,0L1392,0C1344,0,1248,0,1152,0C1056,0,960,0,864,0C768,0,672,0,576,0C480,0,384,0,288,0C192,0,96,0,48,0L0,0Z')


  .container-fluid.reveal(style="margin-top: 40px;padding-top: 30px;padding-bottom: 40px;")
    .row(style="margin-top: 0px;padding-top: 40px;padding-bottom:20px;background: #03000")
      .col-12.col-sm-10.col-md-6.col-lg-6.col-xl-4.offset-xl-1.offset-lg-1.offset-md-0.offset-sm-1.offset-0.row_style
        h3.white_text.sub_heading.reveal(style="margin-bottom: 20px;text-align:center")
          | Who am I? 
        p.white_text.reveal.desc_text
          | I started building this app due to the amount of time I spent searching through movie lists and not knowing what to watch. I built out a basic way to recommend movies that I would like and kept building up from there.
        p.white_text.reveal.desc_text
          | This app is a side project and so we always welcome feedback and contributions. If you have some features you'd like to see please <a href="/contact">contact us here.</a> 
        p.white_text.reveal.desc_text
          | If you have any feedback such as bugs you've noticed we'd also like to hear from you. Of course, if this is something you'd like to contribute code to, then feel more than welcome to get in touch.
        
      .col-10.col-sm-10.col-md-5.col-lg-3.col-xl-3.offset-xl-2.offset-lg-2.offset-md-1.offset-1.align-self-center.row_style.desktop_show
        img(src='/images/headshot1-grey.webp', style="width:100%;border-radius:300px")

